# Walkthrough: RoboLedgers Constitutional Accounting

## 9. Adjusting Journal Entries (Phase 9)
RoboLedgers can now correct the past without rewriting it:
- **[aje.ts](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/adjustments/aje.ts)**: Implements non-mutating additive entries for reclassification.
- **[posting.ts](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/adjustments/posting.ts)**: Enforces balanced math (Sum Debits == Sum Credits) and COA gate rules.
- **[period_rules.ts](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/adjustments/period_rules.ts)**: Ensures AJEs only apply to `LOCKED` periods and provides restated balances.
- **[restatement.ts](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/adjustments/restatement.ts)**: Manages period versions (V1, V2), preserving historical truth.
- **[audit.ts](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/adjustments/audit.ts)**: Provides high-fidelity logs of all adjustments with reason codes.

```bash
